 :crack: [warez d00dz] 1. v. To break into a system (compare {cracker}). 2.
v. Action of removing the copy protection from a commercial program. People
who write cracks consider themselves challenged by the copy protection
measures. They will often do it as much to show that they are smarter than
the developper who designed the copy protection scheme than to actually copy
the program. 3. n. A program, instructions or patch used to remove the copy
protection of a program or to uncripple features from a demo/time limited
program. 4. An {exploit}.